<HEADLINE>
CONSTRUCTION BEGINS ON NCKU HOSPITAL'S SECOND BUILDING
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Jan. 27 (CNA) 01/27/07  16:28:23 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
Construction of the National Cheng Kung University (NCKU)
Hospital's second building, which began Saturday, will be
completed in 2010, a spokesman for the Tainan-based hospital said
at the groundbreaking ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The hospital's second building, with a construction cost of
NT$2.25 billion (US$68.31 million), will include a clinic center,
cancer center, nuclear/clinical medicine center and public
health/environmental medicine center, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Hsu Tientsai, mayor of Tainan City, Chen Chihung, superintendent
of NCKU Hospital, and Kao Chiang, president of the university,
jointly presided over the groundbreaking ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The second building, with three basement levels and 10 storeys,
will boast a floor area of 65,455 square meters and will be
connected to the hospital's first building by a skywalk, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The cancer center is a key development direction for NCKU
Hospital, the spokesman said, adding that the hospital will
integrate systems and improve the quality of cancer treatment.
</P>
